ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It was a great course that I would recommend the course to other students hoping to learn about biochemistry and its applications in the clinical context as illustrated through empirical research.

a course where the relevance of basic/fundamental biochemical topics are demonstrated through clinically-relevant current cases/papers. i would recommend it, since it gives a framework for understanding/thinking about problems
I would definitely recommend the conferences. The lectures were less useful.

A course covering basic techniques and concepts in biochemistry with an emphasis on reading and presenting original research papers. I would recommend it for anyone who is interested in developing skills in journal reading and presentation and for anyone with an interest in biochemistry that would like to go a bit more in depth.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: deepened my understanding of lab-based biochemical techniquesthat may prove useful during my phD
This course solidified my basic understanding of key concepts in biochemistry and helped me to improve my skills in reading, understanding, and presenting papers.
